article.description: Josh Ajayi had 24 points as South Alabama defeated Alabama A&M 89-79 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Ajayi lifts South Alabama over Alabama A&M 89-79
article.linkText: Ajayi lifts South Alabama over Alabama A&M 89-79
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. -- Josh Ajayi had 24 points as South Alabama defeated Alabama A&M 89-79 on Tuesday night. Chad Lott had 17 points for South Alabama (6-4). KK Curry added 15 points and Trhae Mitchell had 4 points, five assists and five blocks. Garrett Hicks had 16 points for the Bulldogs (2-7). Cameron Alford and Jalen Johnson each added 13 points. TJ Parham, who was second on the Bulldogs in scoring entering the contest with 10 points per game, was just 1 of 9 from the field. South Alabama faces Appalachian State at home on Thursday. Alabama A&M faces North Alabama at home on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
